     – Data Layer: PostgreSQL primary DB, Redis cache, Elasticsearch search index  
   • Infrastructure  
     – Docker + Kubernetes (EKS/GKE) for orchestration and auto-scaling  
     – Terraform for IaC, GitHub Actions CI/CD  
     – HTTPS everywhere, Nginx ingress, AWS S3 for static assets

   • Core Entities  
     – Users (id, name, email, hashed_password, role, created_at)  
     – Content (id, user_id, title, body, metadata JSONB, created_at, updated_at)  
     – Sessions (id, user_id, token, expires_at)  
     – ActivityLogs (id, user_id, action, timestamp)  
   • Relationships & Indexing  
     – One-to-many: Users→Content, Users→Sessions, Users→ActivityLogs  
     – JSONB for flexible metadata, GIN indexes on JSONB fields for fast queries  
     – Full-text search via Elasticsearch; periodic sync from PostgreSQL  
   • Caching & Scaling  
     – Redis for session storage, rate-limiting, and frequent lookups  
     – Read-replica for reporting queries  

3. User Experience Optimization  
   • Mobile-First, Responsive Design  
     – Tailwind CSS + component library, fluid grid layouts, touch-friendly interactions  
   • Performance  
     – Code-splitting and lazy loading, image optimization (WebP), HTTP/2, CDN caching  
     – Frontend performance metrics via Lighthouse CI, Real User Monitoring (New Relic)  
   • Accessibility & Usability  
     – WCAG 2.1 AA compliance: ARIA roles, focus management, high-contrast themes  
     – Keyboard navigation, screen-reader labels, semantic HTML  
   • Personalization & Engagement  
     – User dashboard with activity feed and recommendations  
     – Contextual tooltips, guided onboarding tour (Shepherd.js)  
     – A/B testing framework (Optimizely or open-source) to iterate UI variations  
   • Feedback & Analytics  
     – Hotjar heatmaps, session recording, in-app surveys  
     – Analytics events for click paths and feature usage (Segment + Google Analytics)  

4. Testing & Optimization Plan  
   • Automated Testing  
     – Unit tests (Jest, Mocha/pytest), integration tests, and e2e (Cypress/Playwright) in CI pipeline  
   • Performance & Load Testing  
     – Lighthouse CI; WebPageTest in PRs  
     – k6 or JMeter for backend load tests, continuous performance budgets  
   • Monitoring & Error Tracking  
     – Prometheus/Grafana for metrics, Sentry for application errors  
   • Continuous Improvement  
     – Bundle analysis (webpack-bundle-analyzer), image audits  
     – Regular UX reviews, quarterly A/B test sprints, user feedback loops  

This proposal ensures a scalable, resilient architecture; a well-structured, performant database; and a polished, accessible, and data-driven user experience.
